com.blockwithme.util.shared

Class AnyArray

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.blockwithme.util.shared.AnyArray
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Iterable<Any>

    public class AnyArray
extends Object
implements Serializable, Iterable<Any>
    Smallest possible mutable class that could contain a bunch of anything, without requiring "boxing" of primitive values (except long!). Note that it also supports the AnyType.Empty, which allows us to represent "no data", for example, when querying the value of a non-existent property.
    Author:
    monster
    See Also:
